      <div xml:id="NA365-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">(EN: cōkōvaṉār; ET: cokiraṉār)
            itu tōḻi talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉākat talaimakaṭku uraippāḷāy iyaṟpaḻittu iṉṉatu ceytum eṉpāḷāyc colliyatu. [G1+2: itu kēṭṭa talaimakaḷ (G1v: talaimakaṉ) varaivatu payaṉ.]</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said as one talking to HER when HE was behind the fence, being one who, although acting this way, speaks belittling [his] qualities. [G1+2: This has the gist of [HIS] who heard [it] marrying HER.]</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA365">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            aruṅkaṭi yaṉṉai kāva ṉīvip</l>
<l>            peruṅkaṭai yiṟantu maṉṟam pōkip</l>
<l>            pakalē palaruṅ kāṇa nāṇviṭ</l>
<l>            ṭakalvayaṟ paṭappai yavaṉūr viṉavic</l>
<l>            ceṉmō vāḻi tōḻi paṉṉāṭ</l>
<l>            karuvi vāṉam peyyā tāyiṉu</l>
<l>            maruvi yārkku mayantikaḻ cilampiṉ</l>
<l>            vāṉṟōy māmalai nāṭaṉaic</l>
<l>            cāṉṟō yallai yeṉṟaṉam varaṟkē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>            Passing beyond mother’s guarding, severely protective,</l>
<l>            crossing the big gate(?), going to the village common,</l>
<l rend="indent4">                at midday! for many to see shame quit [me],</l>
<l>            asking for his village with gardens [and] wide paddy fields,</l>
<l>            up, oh friend,</l>
<l rend="indent2">                in order to come back after we have said<note place="foot">The construction here is really puzzling. We either have to take it that <term xml:lang="ta">varaṟku</term> is dependent on <term xml:lang="ta">ceṉmō</term> (instead of the habitual double verb form), and then <term xml:lang="ta">eṉṟaṉam</term> must be read as one of the more disturbing kind of <term xml:lang="ta">muṟṟeccam</term>. Or we take the second half as an independent sentence, which would have the advantage that we could take the <term xml:lang="ta">varaṟku</term> as reason for HIS not being worthy ("you are not worthy because of [your] coming [stealthily]), but the disadvantage is that it is hard to make sense of the perfective aspect with <term xml:lang="ta">eṉṟaṉam</term>.</note>:</l>
<l rend="indent2">                “you are not worthy”</l>
<l rend="indent3">                to the man from a land of mountains big as to touch the sky,</l>
<l rend="indent4">                with water-glittering sides where waterfalls roar,</l>
<l rend="indent3">                even if the sky with masses [of clouds] does not rain</l>
<l rend="indent3">                for many days.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
